text:
Just to be clear, with module_block modules I mean these ones:
```{% module_block module "hero_lp_text" path="@HubSpot/rich_text", label="Hero LP Title" %}
  {% module_attribute "html" %}
    &lt;h1 class="lato bold mb0"&gt;Some text&lt;/h1&gt;
  {% end_module_attribute %}
{% end_module_block %}

{% module_block module "logo" path="@HubSpot/image", label="Logo" %}
{% end_module_block %}```
that is HS rich text, images ecc., not custom modules.
<@U04AQA0QM8E> do you think that your idea of maintaining the same modules' names to keep the content unchanged could also apply to the transition module_block -&gt; dnd_module?

Ok, I gather there's no simple and direct way I could turn a standard HTML coded template into a dnd area, isn't it? Unless I place an empty dnd area in a specific point inside the coded template (limiting the customer to be able to add a custom module only there) I guess I'll have to create a new template, convert the present content to dnd modules and hope this will keep the current content intact, right? Gosh :see_no_evil:
